    "updated_at": "2015-02-19T20:12:36Z",
    "body": "IMO, it's not so much about allowing such statics but about allowing `#[static_assert]` on statics that aren't plain integers. You get the same assertion with `struct S { x: i32 }`, and we surely want to allow such statics.\n\nAs far as I'm concerned, I'd forbid `#![static_assert]` on such statics.\n",
